Text.Value: I do. Think of all we've been through just to get to this moment. That wasn't luck. That was us.
I'll look forward to the next 'last kiss'. And the one after that.
I think we're done here. I'll certainly be glad to see the back of it, anyway...
Hardly. We're going to win this, understand? But no sense missing the opportunity...
Honestly? I think self-reflection may be the enemy just now. I can't afford to lose my nerve. Safer to just not think, and keep forging ahead.
If you like. Good thing your practical streak is one of the things I love about you.
I suppose you're right. If things go poorly, this could be the last chance that anyone has to show some affection. Ever. Come here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pre-hug. Staving off emotion. Cusp of final battle.

Text.Value: Always.
Always.
There I was, thinking we were finally about to put an end to all this. Too good to be true, I suppose.
Of course. You look different, there's no denying that... but I think you're still the same, deep down.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere. To player who has become a mind flayer

Text.Value: Leave.
Good. Something for us to look forward to, once all's said and done.
I suppose we can't claim to be shocked - the Emperor's wanted us to embrace our powers the whole time. This is the logical final step.
I'll need a long soak in a bath to rid myself of the feeling of this place. Can I count on you to scrub my back?

EditorData.NodeContext: To romantic partner. In the morphic pool (the cavernous lair of a netherbrain)

Text.Value: I'd offer to take the plunge, but, well... somehow, I don't think Lady Shar would approve of a mind flayer leading her flock.
This could be it. How about a hug, while we still have the chance?
Survival first, flirting later.
Survival first, flirting later.
You're the only one who can make this decision. And whatever you choose, I'll be by your side.
Do you think we can win this?
Do you think we can win this?
This could be my last chance to kiss you.
Let's just stay shoulder to shoulder, and see this through.
The belly of the beast. The sooner we kill this thing, the better.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some foreboding. In the morphic pool (the cavernous lair of a netherbrain)

Text.Value: High Hall. There's nowhere else to go... This is where it all ends, my love.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken to love interest. Steeling her nerves/one last push.In high hall (an upper keep in the city - site of the final sequence of the game)

Text.Value: You're doing what's necessary, for all of us. That's why I've been by your side this whole time.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere. To player who has become a mind flayer

Text.Value: How are you faring?
How are you faring?
I... I can't face the thought of it myself, though. I've only just been able to start living on my own terms... I can't surrender that.
High Hall. There's nowhere else to go... This is where it all ends.
